5115-0141

 

Vysotsky -18

Description of a precious metal coin:

On January 23, 2018, the Bank of Russia issued a commemorative silver coin with a face value of 25 rubles “Creative life by Vladimir Vysotsky” (mass of the precious metal 155.5 g, alloy purity 925, catalog number 5115-0141).

The coin has a round shape with a diameter of 60.0 mm.

Both on the obverse and reverse of the coin, around there is a protruding edge the circumference.

On the front side of the coin, there is a relief image of the State Emblem of the Russian Federation, there are inscriptions: “РОССИЙСКАЯ ФЕДЕРАЦИЯ” (RUSSIAN FEDERATION), “БАНК РОССИИ” (BANK OF RUSSIA), Face value of the coin - “25 РУБЛЕЙ” (25 RUBLES), date – “2018”, metal designation according to the Periodic system of elements D. I. Mendeleev, alloy purity, trademark of the Moscow Mint and the mass of the precious metal.

On the reverse side of the coin are relief images of V.S. Vysotsky with a guitar, to his left – there is a sword and the image of horses made using the laser matting technique. Also, there is an inscription at the circumference at the top “ВЛАДИМИР ВЫСОЦКИЙ” (VLADIMIR VYSOTSKY), below on the right – there are two-line dates “1938” and“1980”.

The edge of the coin is reeded.

The coin has "proof" quality.

The mintage is 1.5 thousand pieces.

The coin is dedicated to the famous Gothic cathedral of Europe, the French Cathedral of Notre Dame (Notre Dame). The design of the coin includes an image of fragments of the architecture of the cathedral, as well as a color image of a circular fragment of one of its stained-glass windows (depicting the Virgin Mary), the imitation of which is achieved by repeating it in a mirror image on the back of the coin.

The greenery surrounding the cathedral is done in color. The reverse depicts (fragmentarily) the main facade of the cathedral and its plan.

On the obverse of the third coin, there is a fragment of the Cathedral in Milan, a top view. The reverse shows a fragment of the main facade of the cathedral, as well as a fragment of the contour image of one of its stained glass windows.

On January 9, 2007, the Bank of Russia issued an investment gold coin with a face value of 50 rubles depicting George the Victorious and the year of issue – 2007.

A gold coin with a face value of 50 rubles (the mass of the precious metal is 7.78 g, purity alloy 999, catalog number 5216-0060) has a round shape with a diameter of 22.6 mm.

On the obverse and reverse of the coin around the circumference there is a protruding edge.

On the obverse of the coin, there is a relief image of the emblem of the Bank of Russia - a two-headed eagle with its wings down, under it there is an inscription in a semicircle " БАНК РОССИИ " (BANK OF RUSSIA) – in a circle framed by a bead rim; also, around the circumference there are inscriptions separated by dots: "ПЯТЬДЕСЯТ РУБЛЕЙ" (FIFTY RUBLES) – the face value of the coin and the year of minting – 2007; between them, there is a metal designation according to the Periodic system of chemical elements Mendeleev, its purity, brand name of the mint and the mass of the precious metal.

On the reverse, the coin has a relief image of George the Victorious on a horse, striking a serpent with a spear.

The edge of the coin is reeded.

The mintage is 500 000 pieces.

Issued coins are the legal tender of the Russian Federation and are required to be accepted at face value in all types of payments without any restrictions.

«B. H. Mayer’s Kunstprageanstalt» (Germany)

The obverse of the coin in the center depicts a jazz ensemble during a performance. The remaining design elements include fragments of stylized portrayals of typical jazz musical instruments: saxophone, trombone and piano. The main inscriptions on the obverse are painted yellow.

The reverse depicts stylized other attributes of jazz creativity: musical instruments: double bass, trumpet and percussion, as well as musical notation and a microphone. At the bottom, there is the inscription "JAZZ" in English and Armenian, made in color.
